  "content": {
    "translations": {
      "en": {
        "tagline": "Electric performance redefined",
        "description_short": "BYD's flagship electric sedan — 5-star Euro NCAP, up to 570km WLTP range, starting from €44,900.",
        "description_long": "The BYD Seal is a D-segment electric sedan built on BYD's e-Platform 3.0, featuring the proprietary Blade Battery with Cell-to-Body (CTB) integration. Launched in China in 2022 and arriving in Europe in 2023, the Seal competes directly with the Tesla Model 3, Hyundai Ioniq 6 and Polestar 2 — offering comparable or superior specifications at a more competitive price point.\n\nAvailable in three variants (Dynamic RWD, Premium RWD and Performance AWD), the Seal covers a wide range of needs — from efficient daily driving to sports sedan performance (0–100 km/h in 3.8 seconds). All variants are equipped with BYD's rotating 15.6-inch touchscreen, wireless CarPlay and Android Auto, and a comprehensive ADAS suite including AEB, ACC, LKA and 360-degree cameras.\n\nThe Seal achieved a maximum five-star Euro NCAP rating in 2023, with 89% adult occupant protection. The Blade Battery uses LFP chemistry, integrated into the vehicle's structure for enhanced rigidity, with an 8-year/160,000km warranty.",
        "key_selling_points": [
          "5-star Euro NCAP (2023) — 89% adult occupant protection",
          "Blade Battery LFP — safer and longer-lasting than NMC",
          "Up to 570km WLTP range on the 82.5kWh battery",
          "0–100 km/h in 3.8 sec (Performance AWD)",
          "From €44,900 — strong value vs Tesla Model 3"
        ],
        "seo_title": "BYD Seal 2025 – Electric Sedan Specs, Range & Prices | ChinaCars.Global",
        "seo_description": "BYD Seal: 5-star Euro NCAP, up to 570km range, from €44,900. Full specs, all variants, prices in 20+ markets. Compare with Tesla Model 3 and Ioniq 6."
      },
